  "prompt": "Google Nexus 7: How to change default action for playing video from Engadget app? I have chosen YouTube but it doesn't play. My HTC One X uses streaming media player. How to change this default action to streaming media player?",
  "response": "To change the default action for playing videos from the Engadget app on your Google Nexus 7, follow these steps:\n\n### Step 1: Clear Default App Settings\n1. **Open Settings**: Go to the Settings app on your Nexus 7.\n2. **Apps/Application Manager**: Scroll down and tap on **Apps** or **Application Manager** (depending on your Android version).\n3. Find the **Engadget App**: Scroll through the list of apps and tap on the Engadget app.\n4. **Clear Defaults**: Look for an option called **Clear Defaults** or **Set as Default** and tap it. This will remove any previously set default actions for the app.\n\n### Step 2: Change Default Action to Streaming Media Player\n1. **Open Engadget App**: Launch the Engadget app and find a video to play.\n2. **Select Action**: When you tap to play the video, you should see a dialog asking you to choose how to play it (e.g., YouTube, Streaming Media Player, etc.).\n3. **Choose Streaming Media Player**: Select the **Streaming Media Player** option.\n4. **Set as Default**: Check the box that says **Always** or **Use by default for this action** to set the Streaming Media Player as the default for all similar actions.\n\n### Step 3: Verify the Change\n1. **Test the Video**: Try playing another video in the Engadget app to ensure it opens in the Streaming Media Player.\n\n### If the Problem Persists\nIf the video still doesn\u2019t play or the Streaming Media Player isn\u2019t listed as an option:\n1. **Update Apps**: Make sure both the Engadget app and the Streaming Media Player are up to date.\n2. **Check Permissions**: Ensure the Streaming Media Player has the necessary permissions to play videos.\n3. **Reinstall Apps**: If issues continue, try uninstalling and reinstalling the Engadget app and the Streaming Media Player.\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
